effective_detector_rules.description: User logged in from a known list of malicious IP blocks which can be a potential threat.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the user is a genuinely logged in user and the credentials are not compromised. This can be done by enabling Multi Factor Authentication (MFA).

effective_detector_rules.description: Auth tokens can be used to authenticate with third-party APIs. This detector creates a problem whenever an Auth token is created for a user. They can be created by users themselves or by an admin with the right privileges.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure these keys or credentials are being created by and for authorized users.

effective_detector_rules.description: Network security groups (NSGs) act as a virtual firewall for compute instances and other kinds of resources. NSGs have a set of inbound (ingress) and outbound (egress) security rules applied to a set of virtual NICs in a VCN. Deleting NSGs can remove protections between resources in the VCN.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the removal of the NSG is permitted for this VCN and its related resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Network security groups (NSGs) act as a virtual firewall for compute instances and other kinds of resources. NSGs have a set of inbound (ingress) and outbound (egress) security rules applied to a set of virtual NICs in a VCN. Changes to NSGs egress rules may allow connections and traffic to new resources and VNICs in the VCN.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: VCN Network Security Group egress rule changed
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the new egress rules are permitted for this NSG and its related resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Certificate Authorities are the root of trust for all certificates issued by the CA. To prevent any service impacts where leaf certificates of the CA are being used, CA deletion should only be performed by authorized personnel. All certificates the Certificate Authority (CA) issued will have to be deleted before you can delete the CA.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Make sure the deletion was done by an expected user. If not authorized, cancel the scheduled deletion of the CA.

effective_detector_rules.description: A Bastion Session provides secure and time-bound access to the customers target host.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: A session allows users to access the target hosts via the bastion so ensure the session is created by the authorized user.

effective_detector_rules.description: Bastions provides users with secure and seamless ssh access to target hosts in private subnets thus restricting direct public access. This detector creates a problem when a new Bastion instance has been created.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure the bastions are created by the right admins/users and this operation is permitted by them.

effective_detector_rules.description: IAM OAuth 2.0 credentials are for interacting with the APIs of those services that use OAuth 2.0 authorization. This detector creates a problem whenever an OAuth 2.0 credential is created for a user. They can be created by users themselves or by an admin with the right privileges.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure these keys or credentials are being created by and for authorized users.

effective_detector_rules.description: API keys are needed if you are using one of Oracle SDKs or tools. This detector creates a problem whenever an API key is created for a user. It can be created by users themselves or by an admin with the right privileges.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure these keys or credentials are being created by and for authorized users.

effective_detector_rules.description: Triggers a problem when a user creates or resets their Console password. Any user with the corresponding IAM manage privileges can also reset other user's password.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: IAM User UI password created or reset
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Resetting a password too many times of resetting other's credentials could be a possible security alert hence ensure this action is permitted by the correct user.

effective_detector_rules.description: Triggers a Cloud Guard problem when a user revokes an Intermediate CA. Revoking an intermediate would incur all its leaf certificates unusable. This is an operation that needs to be done by authorized personal while making sure it's not impacting any of your existing workloads. All certificates the Certificate Authority (CA) issued will no longer be valid if a Certificate Revocation List (CRL) was configured.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Make sure the revocation was done by an expected user. Ensure all subordinate Certificate Authority (CA) versions and certificate versions created by the revoked CA are not in use. When the new CRL is hosted, the validation for any of the revoked CA's descendants will fail. Users should issue a new, uncompromised CA version and rebuild the descendant hierarchy using newly issued resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: A VCN (virtual cloud network) is a virtual, private network that you set up in Oracle data centers. Like a traditional network, it may contain firewall rules and specific types of communication gateways.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the creation of a new VCN is permitted and expected in this compartment.

effective_detector_rules.description: IAM OAuth 2.0 credentials are for interacting with the APIs of those services that use OAuth 2.0 authorization. This detector creates a problem whenever an OAuth 2.0 credential is deleted for a user.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure these keys or credentials are being deleted by and for authorized users.

effective_detector_rules.description: API keys are needed if you are using one of Oracle SDKs or tools. This detector creates a problem whenever an API key is deleted for a user. It can be deleted by users themselves or by an admin with the right privileges.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure these keys or credentials are being deleted by and for authorized users.

effective_detector_rules.description: Security lists act as virtual firewalls for compute instances and other resources and consists of sets of ingress and egress rules that apply to all the VNICs in any subnet associated with that security list. Multiple security lists may apply to resources and give access to ports and IP addresses for those resources.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the removal of this security list is permitted for this VCN and its related resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Groups may control access to resources and privileges. This detector rule triggers a problem when an IAM group is deleted.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Groups may control access to resources and privileges, hence any group deletion should be monitored.

effective_detector_rules.description: DRG or Dynamic Routing gateways are used when connecting your existing on-premises network to your virtual cloud network (VCN) with IPSEC VPN or FastConnect. This detector triggers a problem when a DRG is deleted.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the deletion of a DRG is permitted by the resource (User).

effective_detector_rules.description: Subnets are subnet a subdivision of a VCN. Subnets may connect Compute instances in a given subnet use the same route table, security lists, and DHCP options.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the change to the VCN is permitted and expected in this compartment.

effective_detector_rules.description: An IAM user can be an individual employee or system that needs to manage or use your company's Oracle Cloud Infrastructure resources.This detector triggers a problem when a local or federated user is created in OCI IAM.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the creation of a new user is permitted and expected to be created by the user who did this operation.

effective_detector_rules.description: DHCP options control certain types of configuration on the instances in a VCN. These include the specification of search domains and DNS resolvers, which can direct communications within VCNs across to Internet resources.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the change to DHCP and DNS information is permitted for this VCN and related resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Compute instances may deliver critical functions.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the termination of the compute instance is sanctioned and performed by a permitted administrator.

effective_detector_rules.description: A new CA bundle is updated via API. A CA bundle is the chain of trust for your resources. If your resource receives a certificate created by a CA in the chain of trust the certificate will be accepted.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: CA bundle content has been updated. Verify this is correct. A CA Bundle is the chain of trust from which your resources will accept certificates. Ensure your bundle has the correct information for your trusted resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Changes to policies apply to all members within the scope of the policy and may be granted to users who do not require them.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the policy is restricted to allow only specific users to access the resources required to accomplish their job functions and the modification was sanctioned.

effective_detector_rules.description: Database systems may hold sensitive data and provide critical functionality. Termination of a database system permanently deletes the system, any databases running on it, and any storage volumes attached to it.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the termination of the database system and related databases is sanctioned and performed by a permitted administrator.

effective_detector_rules.description: VCN local peering gateways (LPG) connect 2 VCNs in the same region without routing traffic over the internet. This allows resources in the VCNs to communicate directly with private IP addresses. Changes to LPGs can impact resource access and cross-VCN communications.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the changes to the LPGs are permitted for this VCN and its related resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Compute images are the foundations for compute instances. A modifications to images impacts every future compute instance launched from that image. Images and any changes related to them should come from known and trusted sources.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the compute image change was expected and performed by a trusted administrator permitted to make the change in your environment.

effective_detector_rules.description: Groups may control access to resources and privileges. Sensitive groups should be closely monitored for membership changes
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the user is entitled to be a member of the group.

effective_detector_rules.description: A VCN (virtual cloud network) is a virtual, private network that you set up in Oracle data centers. Like a traditional network, it may contain firewall rules and specific types of communication gateways.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the deletion of a VCN is permitted and expected in this compartment.

effective_detector_rules.description: Attaching a DRG (Dynamic Routing gateways) to a VCN  provides a path for private traffic between your VCN and networks outside your VCN, for example your on-prem network. This detector ensures users are aware of the additional connectivity in their network.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that attaching of this DRG to the VCN is permitted and expected in this compartment by the resource (User).

effective_detector_rules.description: Internet gateways are virtual routers you can add to your VCN to enable direct connectivity (inbound from or outbound) to the internet.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the deletion of an internet gateway is permitted for this VCN and its related resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Compute images are the foundations for compute instances. A new image impacts every future compute instance launched from that image and imported images should come from known and trusted sources.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the compute image being imported is from a trusted sources like Oracle or trusted compute administrator and that it was imported by a person expected to bring new images into your environment.

effective_detector_rules.description: To access Oracle Cloud Infrastructure, a user must have the required credentials like API keys, auth tokens and other credentials. An IAM administrator can enable/disable these capabilities for individual users. This detector rule triggers a problem when such capabilities are modified.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the "User capabilities" are allowed to be enabled/disabled for these users.

effective_detector_rules.description: Groups may control access to resources and privileges. This detector rule triggers a problem when a new IAM group is created.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Groups may control access to resources and privileges, hence any group creation should be monitored.

effective_detector_rules.description: Internet gateways are virtual routers you can add to your VCN to enable direct connectivity (inbound from or outbound) to the internet.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the creation of an internet gateway is permitted for this VCN and its related resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Customer secret keys are created for Amazon S3 Compatibility API with Object Storage. This detector creates a problem whenever a Customer secret key is created for a user. They can be created by users themselves or by an admin with the right privileges.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure these keys or credentials are being created by and for authorized users.

effective_detector_rules.description: Removing a user from a group need to be an authorized action and should be done by a user or admin with the right privileges. This detector creates a problem when the operation is done by a user.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the group memberships modifications are done by the authorized users.

effective_detector_rules.description: Attaching a DRG (Dynamic Routing gateways) to a VCN  provides a path for private traffic between your VCN and networks outside your VCN, for example your on-prem network. This detector triggers a problem when such DRG attachment to a VCN has been removed.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that detaching of this DRG component from your VCN is permitted by the resource (User).

effective_detector_rules.description: Customer secret keys are created for Amazon S3 Compatibility API with Object Storage. This detector creates a problem whenever a Customer secret key is deleted for a user.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure these keys or credentials are being deleted by and for authorized users.

effective_detector_rules.description: DRG or Dynamic Routing gateways are used when connecting your existing on-premises network to your virtual cloud network (VCN) with IPSEC VPN or FastConnect. This detector triggers a problem when a new DRG is created.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the creation of a new DRG is permitted and expected in this compartment by the resource (User).

effective_detector_rules.description: Auth tokens can be used to authenticate with third-party APIs. This detector creates a problem whenever an Auth token is deleted for a user.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure these keys or credentials are being deleted by and for authorized users.

effective_detector_rules.description: Virtual route tables have rules that look and act like traditional network route rules. Misconfigured route tables may send network traffic to be dropped (blackholed) or sent to an unintended target.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the change to the route table is permitted and expected in this compartment.

effective_detector_rules.description: Compute images may be equivalent to "data drives" and contain sensitive information. Images that may contain anything proprietary should be identified accordingly with export privileges permitted only to suitable OCI administrators.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Images that contain anything proprietary should be tagged accordingly with export privileges allowed only to suitable OCI administrators.

effective_detector_rules.description: Security lists act as virtual firewalls for compute instances and other resources and consists of sets of ingress and egress rules that apply to all the VNICs in any subnet associated with that security list. Multiple security lists may apply to resources and give access to ports and IP addresses for those resources.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the creation of this security list is permitted for this VCN and its related resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Network security groups (NSGs) act as a virtual firewall for compute instances and other kinds of resources. NSGs have a set of inbound (ingress) and outbound (egress) security rules applied to a set of virtual NICs in a VCN. Changes to NSGs ingress rules may allow connections and traffic to new resources and VNICs in the VCN.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: VCN Network Security Group ingress rule changed
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the new ingress rules are permitted for this NSG and its related resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Security lists act as virtual firewalls for compute instances and other resources and consists of sets of ingress and egress rules that apply to all the VNICs in any subnet associated with that security list. Multiple security lists may apply to resources and give access to ports and IP addresses for those resources.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: VCN Security List egress rules changed
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the changes to the egress rules are permitted for this security list and its related resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Security lists act as virtual firewalls for compute instances and other resources and consists of sets of ingress and egress rules that apply to all the VNICs in any subnet associated with that security list. Multiple security lists may apply to resources and give access to ports and IP addresses for those resources.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: VCN Security List ingress rules changed
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the changes to the ingress rules are permitted for this security list and its related resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Subnets are subnet a subdivision of a VCN. Subnets may connect Compute instances in a given subnet use the same route table, security lists, and DHCP options. Removing a subnet is equivalent to removing a network segment.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the removal of the VCN subnet is permitted and expected in this compartment.

effective_detector_rules.description: Multi-factor authentication (MFA) increases security by requiring compromise of more than one credential to impersonate a user. Unauthorized users will be unable to meet the second authentication requirement and will not be able to access the environment.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the login attempt is performed by an authorised user

attributes.description: This is an Oracle managed Oracle Cloud Infrastructure recipe with configuration detector rules. To create your own recipe, clone an existing Oracle managed recipe from the root compartment

effective_detector_rules.description: This detector rule identifies all instances that have a public IP assigned and reside on a public subnet reachable via an Internet Gateway, has a route table entry to the Internet Gateway and allows traffic from "All protocols"
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Carefully consider allowing internet access to any instances. For an instance to be publicly addressable, it must have a public IP, exist in a public VCN subnet or in VCN NSG ingress security rule, the VCN must have an Internet Gateway enabled and be configured for outbound traffic and the security list for the subnet must be configured for all IPs and all ports (0.0.0.0/0).

effective_detector_rules.description: Checks public IP only
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Instance has a public IP address
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Carefully consider allowing internet access to any instances. For example, you do not want to accidentally allow internet access to sensitive database instances.

effective_detector_rules.description: Untagged resources in OCI indicate that infrastructure has been created without the use of corporate-sanctioned tags. Uncontrolled infrastructure can result in a weakened security posture. Alert if an untagged resource is found. Resource types that will trigger an alert if untagged: compute images (IMAGE), compute instances (INSTANCE), database systems (DB_SYSTEM), VCNs (VCN), object storage (BUCKET), and storage block volumes (VOLUME).
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Verify that the configured tags are in use for compute images, compute instances, database systems, VCNs, object storage, and storage block volumes.

effective_detector_rules.description: This detector rule identifies all database systems that have a public IP assigned and reside on a public subnet reachable via an Internet Gateway and allows traffic from "All protocols"
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Carefully consider allowing internet access to any database system. For a database system to be publicly addressable, it must have a public IP, exist in a public VCN subnet or in VCN NSG ingress security rule, the VCN must have an Internet Gateway enabled and be configured for outbound traffic and the security list for the subnet must be configured for all IPs and all ports (0.0.0.0/0).

effective_detector_rules.description: Changing IAM Auth Tokens at least every 90 days is a security best practice. The longer that IAM credentials remain unchanged, the greater the risk that they can become compromised.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: IAM Auth token is too old
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Rotate IAM Auth token regularly, at least every 90 days.

effective_detector_rules.description: This identifies all instances built from Oracle public images. Platform Images, Oracle Images and Partner images are considered as Oracle public images.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Instance is running an Oracle public image
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that your instances are all running sanctioned images from trusted sources.

effective_detector_rules.description: For information security, you should periodically change or rotate, passwords, keys, and cryptographic materials. Rotating your keys in vault reduces the impact and probability of key compromise.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that you rotate the vault keys regularly.

effective_detector_rules.description: Use of a public IP address to access a database increases your exposure to potential security and business continuity risks.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Database System has public IP address
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the database system does not have a public IP address.

effective_detector_rules.description: IAM group membership frequently grants access to resources and features. Group memberships that have too many members may represent overly permissive privileges being given to too many users.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: IAM group has too many members
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Review the group membership and related privileges to ensure that excessive privileges or overly broad memberships to privileges are not present.

effective_detector_rules.description: If your OCI tenancy uses tags as a control for your environment, this control will alert when an instance is running without required tags.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Instance is running without required Tags
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the instances are using required tags.

effective_detector_rules.description: Data Safe helps ensure your databases are securely configured. This service should be activated to help monitor, secure, and mitigate risks inside your Oracle cloud databases.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Enable Data Safe and configure assessments to evaluate and monitor configuration, check user activities, and mitigate risks.

effective_detector_rules.description: Running unsanctioned versions of DB Systems may increase your chances of a security breach, putting your data confidentiality, integrity, and availability at risk.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Database System version is not sanctioned
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Oracle recommends that the deployed Database system version is approved and tested.

effective_detector_rules.description: Changing IAM Console password at least every 90 days is a security best practice. The longer that IAM credentials remain unchanged, the greater the risk that they can become compromised.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Rotate IAM Console password regularly, at least every 90 days.

effective_detector_rules.description: Multifactor authentication provides an additional layer of security, on top of user name and password. A second verification factor is required each time a user logs in. During the authentication process, users can enable a single device as a trusted device for a maximum period of one day. The email passcode must not be valid for more than 10 minutes. All this provides a degree of protection from password spraying, credential stuffing, and account takeover attacks.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: User does not have MFA enabled
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Enable MFA for all users, using the Oracle Mobile Authenticator (OMA) application on each user's mobile device and the one-time passcode (OTP) sent to the user's registered email address.

effective_detector_rules.description: Complex passwords are harder to guess and can decrease the chances of unauthorized access or compromised data.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Password policy does not meet complexity requirements
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Oracle recommends that a strong password policy include combination of the lower and upper case alphabets, numbers and special characters with appropriate password length. Enable right policy rules under Identity -> Authentication settings

effective_detector_rules.description: This detector rule triggers a problem when the cipher suite configured for the load balancer's listener is oci-wider-compatible-ssl-cipher-suite-v1. This cipher suite includes algorithms like DES and RC4, which are largely considered weak and are prone to attacks. This detector is only applicable for predefined Cipher suites and not the Custom cipher suite values.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Load balancer allows weak cipher suite
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Recommended to use default/modern/compatible cipher suites that support stronger encryption.

effective_detector_rules.description: Network security groups (NSGs) act as a virtual firewall for compute instances and other kinds of resources. NSGs inbound (ingress) security rules apply to a set of virtual NICs in a VCN to allow access to specific ports and IP addresses.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: NSG ingress rule contains disallowed IP/port
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the ingress rules for communication with the IP/port are permitted for this NSG.

effective_detector_rules.description: Changing IAM Customer secret keys at least every 90 days is a security best practice. The longer that IAM credentials remain unchanged, the greater the risk that they can become compromised.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: IAM Customer secret key is too old
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Rotate IAM Customer secret  keys regularly, at least every 90 days.

effective_detector_rules.description: To ensure continuous security and usability, SSL certificates must be rotated in OCI.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Load balancer SSL certificate expiring soon
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that certificates are rotated on a timely basis.

effective_detector_rules.description: Gateways provide external connectivity to hosts in a VCN. They include Internet Gateway (IGW) for Internet connectivity.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that internet gateways are authorized to be attached to a VCN, and that this attachment doesnt expose resources to the internet. Ensure that security lists with ingress / inbound rules and those security lists are not configured to allow access from all IP addresses 0.0.0.0/0.

effective_detector_rules.description: IAM group membership frequently grants access to resources and features. Group memberships that have too few members may represent excess privileges being "orphaned".
effective_detector_rules.display_name: IAM group has too few members
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Review the group membership related privileges to ensure that excessive or orphaned privileges are not present.

effective_detector_rules.description: Database system patches often include updates that eliminate known security vulnerabilities. Raise a problem when a database system is discovered which has one or more patches, available for 90 days or more, that have not been applied.

configurations.name: Number of days to apply patch

effective_detector_rules.display_name: Database system patch is not applied
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Oracle recommends that released patches be applied to the DB system as soon as possible.

effective_detector_rules.description: Database patches address functionality, security, and performance issues. The vast majority of security breaches can be prevented by applying available patches.

configurations.name: Number of days to apply patch

effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Oracle recommends that released patches be applied to the database as soon as possible.

effective_detector_rules.description: A back-end set is a logical entity defined by a load balancing policy, a health check policy, and a list of back-end servers.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Load balancer has no back-end set
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that you configure load balancers with back-end sets to control the health and access to a load balancer by defined instances.

effective_detector_rules.description: Prerequisite: Create a Host Scan Recipe and a Host Scan Target in the Scanning service. The Scanning service scans compute hosts to identify known cybersecurity vulnerabilities related to applications, libraries, operating systems, and services. This detector triggers a problem when the Scanning service has reported that an instance has one or more CRITICAL (or lower severity, based on the Input Settings within the detector config) vulnerabilities.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Patch the reported CVE's detected on host by performing actions recommended for each CVE.

effective_detector_rules.description: Encryption of volumes provides an additional level of security on your data. Management of encryption keys is critical to protecting and accessing protected data. Some customers want to identify Block Volumes encrypted Oracle-managed keys in order to apply their own key lifecycle management to the volume.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Block Volume is encrypted with Oracle-managed key
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Assign a vault key to this volume

effective_detector_rules.description: Network security groups (NSGs) act as a virtual firewall for compute instances and other kinds of resources. NSGs outbound (egress) security rules apply to a set of virtual NICs in a VCN to allow access to specific ports and IP addresses.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: NSG egress rule contains disallowed IP/port
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the egress rules for communication with the IP/port are permitted for this NSG.

effective_detector_rules.description: Detector triggers a problem when the write access logs are not enabled for an Object Storage bucket. Access logs help customers secure their sensitive objects by providing visibility into the activities around read and write operations of the objects within the Object storage bucket.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Write Log access disabled for bucket
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure write logs are enabled for the bucket and the logs are being continuously monitored by the security tools.

effective_detector_rules.description: Prerequisite: Create a Host Scan Recipe and a Host Scan Target in the Scanning service. The Scanning service scans compute hosts to identify open ports. This detector triggers a problem when the Scanning service has reported that an instance has one or more open ports. Certain ports are required for operation and delivery of services but any open port beyond the intended list can potentially be used to exploit the services. You can modify the default list of allowed ports or disallowed ports in Input Settings within the detector.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Review if identified ports should be open on this host and close them if they are not required to be open.

effective_detector_rules.description: This detector rule triggers a problem when the protocol configured as part of SSL policy for the load balancer's listener includes any version lesser than TLS 1.2. Older versions of Transport Layer Security are extremely risky and vulnerable to many attacks. The use of TLS 1.2+ is strongly encouraged by several standards like PCI-DSS and NIST.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Load balancer allows weak SSL communication
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the SSL policy version configured for load balancer's listener is at least TLS1.2.

effective_detector_rules.description: A virtual network interface card (VNIC) isa networking component that enables a resource such as a compute instance to connect to a virtual cloud network (VCN). The VNIC determines how the instance connects with endpoints inside and outside the VCN. Each VNIC resides in a subnet in a VCN. An VNIC with an NSG may trigger a connectivity issue.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: VNIC without associated network security group
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the missing NSG association from this VNIC is expected.

effective_detector_rules.description: Default tenancy administrator group members can perform any action on all resources in that tenancy. This high-privilege entitlement must be controlled and restricted to only those users who need it to perform their job functions.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Tenancy admin privilege granted to group
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Verify with the OCI administrator that this entitlement grant was sanctioned and that the membership of the group remains valid after the grant of the administrator privilege.

effective_detector_rules.description: Encryption of storage buckets provides an additional level of security on your data. Management of encryption keys is critical to protecting and accessing protected data. Some customers want to identify storage buckets encrypted Oracle-managed keys in order to apply their own key lifecycle management to the bucket.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Object Storage bucket is encrypted with Oracle-managed key
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Assign a vault key to this bucket

effective_detector_rules.description: Data Safe helps ensure your databases are securely configured. An Oracle cloud database has been discovered that is not yet registered with Data Safe.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Database is not registered in Data Safe
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Register this database instance with Data Safe and configure assessments to evaluate and monitor configuration, check user activities, and mitigate risks.

effective_detector_rules.description: Security lists provide stateful and stateless firewall capability to control network access to your instances. A security list is configured at the subnet level and enforced at the instance level. You can apply multiple security lists to a subnet where a network packet is allowed if it matches any rule in the security lists.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: VCN has no inbound Security List
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that your OCI VCNs use security lists with ingress or inbound rules to only allow access from known resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Object Storage supports anonymous, unauthenticated access to a bucket. A public bucket that has read access enabled for anonymous users allows anyone to obtain object metadata, download bucket objects, and optionally list bucket contents.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the bucket is sanctioned for public access, and if not, direct the OCI administrator to restrict the bucket policy to allow only specific users access to the resources required to accomplish their job functions.

effective_detector_rules.description: OCI load balancers enable end-to-end TLS connections between a client's applications and your VCN. A listener is a logical entity that checks for incoming traffic on the load balancer's IP address. To handle TCP, HTTP, and HTTPS traffic, you must configure at least one listener per traffic type.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Load balancer has no inbound rules or listeners
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that your OCI load balancers use inbound rules or listeners to only allow access from known resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Use VCN security lists to restrict network access to instances in a subnet. To prevent unauthorized access or attacks on compute instances, Oracle recommends that you use a VCN security list to allow SSH or RDP access only from authorized ICIDR blocks, rather than leaving them open to the internet (0.0.0.0/0)
effective_detector_rules.display_name: VCN Security list allows traffic to non-public port from all sources (0.0.0.0/0)
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: To prevent unauthorized access or attacks on compute instances, Oracle recommends that you use a VCN security list to allow SSH or RDP access only from authorized CIDR blocks, rather than leaving them open to the internet (0.0.0.0/0).

effective_detector_rules.description: Changing IAM API keys at least every 90 days is a security best practice. The longer that IAM credentials remain unchanged, the greater the risk that they can become compromised.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Rotate API keys regularly, at least every 90 days.

effective_detector_rules.description: Enabling automatic backup ensures that you will be able to restore the database with minimal data loss, if there is a catastrophic hardware failure.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Database is not backed up automatically
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that automatic backup is enabled.

effective_detector_rules.description: Detector triggers a problem when the read access logs are not enabled for an Object Storage bucket. Access logs help customers secure their sensitive objects by providing visibility into the activities around read and write operations of the objects within the Object storage bucket.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Read Log access disabled for bucket
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure read logs are enabled for the bucket and the logs are being continuously monitored by the security tools.

effective_detector_rules.description: This detector rule triggers a problem when traffic is allowed to certain restricted ports (see Input Settings, Restricted Protocol:Ports List) as part of the Security list ingress rule. If "Restricted Protocol:Ports List" includes port values that are identified or allowed for your workloads, then modify the list of ports in Input Settings accordingly.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: VCN Security list allows traffic to restricted port
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Additional details section of the problem provides a list of open Restricted ports that triggered this problem. Ensure that your OCI VCNs use security lists with ingress or inbound rules to only allow traffic access to identified ports. Review if detected ports should be open on this security list Ingress rule and close them if they are not required to be open. It is also recommended to check the "Restricted Protocol:Ports List" in the Input setting of this detector rule and modify it to allow certain required ports and thus notifying Cloud Guard to not detect a problem for those ports.

effective_detector_rules.description: Detaching a block volume decouples the volume from its associated instance and could affect data available. This could affect data availability from business-critical data to point-in-time copies of volumes as backups.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the block volume is not required to be attached to a compute instance for proper operation.

effective_detector_rules.description: Prerequisite: Create a Container Scan Recipe and a Container Scan Target in the Scanning service. The Scanning service scans OCIR images to identify known cybersecurity vulnerabilities related to applications, libraries, operating systems, and services. This detector triggers a problem when the Scanning service has reported that an image has one or more CRITICAL (or lower severity, based on the Input Settings within the detector config) vulnerabilities.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Patch the reported CVE's detected on image by performing actions recommended for each CVE.

effective_detector_rules.description: Use of a public IP address to access a load balancer increases your exposure to potential security and business continuity risks.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Load Balancer has public IP address
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the load balancer have a public IP address only if it is necessary.

effective_detector_rules.description: Gateways provide external connectivity to hosts in a VCN. They include Local Peering Gateway (LPG) for connectivity to peered VCN.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: VCN has Local Peering Gateway attached
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that local peering gateways are authorized to be attached to a VCN, and that this attachment doesnt expose resources to the internet.

effective_detector_rules.description: The sanctioned version of a database has the most recent security features and vulnerability patches.

effective_detector_rules.description: This detector rule identifies all instances that have a public IP assigned and reside on a public subnet reachable via an Internet Gateway, has a route table entry to the Internet Gateway and allows traffic from "All protocols"
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Carefully consider allowing internet access to any instances. For an instance to be publicly addressable, it must have a public IP, exist in a public VCN subnet or in VCN NSG ingress security rule, the VCN must have an Internet Gateway enabled and be configured for outbound traffic and the security list for the subnet must be configured for all IPs and all ports (0.0.0.0/0).

effective_detector_rules.description: Checks public IP only
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Instance has a public IP address
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Carefully consider allowing internet access to any instances. For example, you do not want to accidentally allow internet access to sensitive database instances.

effective_detector_rules.description: Untagged resources in OCI indicate that infrastructure has been created without the use of corporate-sanctioned tags. Uncontrolled infrastructure can result in a weakened security posture. Alert if an untagged resource is found. Resource types that will trigger an alert if untagged: compute images (IMAGE), compute instances (INSTANCE), database systems (DB_SYSTEM), VCNs (VCN), object storage (BUCKET), and storage block volumes (VOLUME).
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Verify that the configured tags are in use for compute images, compute instances, database systems, VCNs, object storage, and storage block volumes.

effective_detector_rules.description: This detector rule identifies all database systems that have a public IP assigned and reside on a public subnet reachable via an Internet Gateway and allows traffic from "All protocols"
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Carefully consider allowing internet access to any database system. For a database system to be publicly addressable, it must have a public IP, exist in a public VCN subnet or in VCN NSG ingress security rule, the VCN must have an Internet Gateway enabled and be configured for outbound traffic and the security list for the subnet must be configured for all IPs and all ports (0.0.0.0/0).

effective_detector_rules.description: Changing IAM Auth Tokens at least every 90 days is a security best practice. The longer that IAM credentials remain unchanged, the greater the risk that they can become compromised.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: IAM Auth token is too old
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Rotate IAM Auth token regularly, at least every 90 days.

effective_detector_rules.description: This identifies all instances built from Oracle public images. Platform Images, Oracle Images and Partner images are considered as Oracle public images.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Instance is running an Oracle public image
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that your instances are all running sanctioned images from trusted sources.

effective_detector_rules.description: For information security, you should periodically change or rotate, passwords, keys, and cryptographic materials. Rotating your keys in vault reduces the impact and probability of key compromise.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that you rotate the vault keys regularly.

effective_detector_rules.description: Use of a public IP address to access a database increases your exposure to potential security and business continuity risks.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Database System has public IP address
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the database system does not have a public IP address.

effective_detector_rules.description: IAM group membership frequently grants access to resources and features. Group memberships that have too many members may represent overly permissive privileges being given to too many users.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: IAM group has too many members
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Review the group membership and related privileges to ensure that excessive privileges or overly broad memberships to privileges are not present.

effective_detector_rules.description: If your OCI tenancy uses tags as a control for your environment, this control will alert when an instance is running without required tags.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Instance is running without required Tags
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the instances are using required tags.

effective_detector_rules.description: Data Safe helps ensure your databases are securely configured. This service should be activated to help monitor, secure, and mitigate risks inside your Oracle cloud databases.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Enable Data Safe and configure assessments to evaluate and monitor configuration, check user activities, and mitigate risks.

effective_detector_rules.description: Running unsanctioned versions of DB Systems may increase your chances of a security breach, putting your data confidentiality, integrity, and availability at risk.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Database System version is not sanctioned
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Oracle recommends that the deployed Database system version is approved and tested.

effective_detector_rules.description: Changing IAM Console password at least every 90 days is a security best practice. The longer that IAM credentials remain unchanged, the greater the risk that they can become compromised.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Rotate IAM Console password regularly, at least every 90 days.

effective_detector_rules.description: Multifactor authentication provides an additional layer of security, on top of user name and password. A second verification factor is required each time a user logs in. During the authentication process, users can enable a single device as a trusted device for a maximum period of one day. The email passcode must not be valid for more than 10 minutes. All this provides a degree of protection from password spraying, credential stuffing, and account takeover attacks.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: User does not have MFA enabled
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Enable MFA for all users, using the Oracle Mobile Authenticator (OMA) application on each user's mobile device and the one-time passcode (OTP) sent to the user's registered email address.

effective_detector_rules.description: Complex passwords are harder to guess and can decrease the chances of unauthorized access or compromised data.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Password policy does not meet complexity requirements
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Oracle recommends that a strong password policy include combination of the lower and upper case alphabets, numbers and special characters with appropriate password length. Enable right policy rules under Identity -> Authentication settings

effective_detector_rules.description: This detector rule triggers a problem when the cipher suite configured for the load balancer's listener is oci-wider-compatible-ssl-cipher-suite-v1. This cipher suite includes algorithms like DES and RC4, which are largely considered weak and are prone to attacks. This detector is only applicable for predefined Cipher suites and not the Custom cipher suite values.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Load balancer allows weak cipher suite
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Recommended to use default/modern/compatible cipher suites that support stronger encryption.

effective_detector_rules.description: Network security groups (NSGs) act as a virtual firewall for compute instances and other kinds of resources. NSGs inbound (ingress) security rules apply to a set of virtual NICs in a VCN to allow access to specific ports and IP addresses.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: NSG ingress rule contains disallowed IP/port
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the ingress rules for communication with the IP/port are permitted for this NSG.

effective_detector_rules.description: Changing IAM Customer secret keys at least every 90 days is a security best practice. The longer that IAM credentials remain unchanged, the greater the risk that they can become compromised.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: IAM Customer secret key is too old
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Rotate IAM Customer secret  keys regularly, at least every 90 days.

effective_detector_rules.description: To ensure continuous security and usability, SSL certificates must be rotated in OCI.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Load balancer SSL certificate expiring soon
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that certificates are rotated on a timely basis.

effective_detector_rules.description: Gateways provide external connectivity to hosts in a VCN. They include Internet Gateway (IGW) for Internet connectivity.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that internet gateways are authorized to be attached to a VCN, and that this attachment doesnt expose resources to the internet. Ensure that security lists with ingress / inbound rules and those security lists are not configured to allow access from all IP addresses 0.0.0.0/0.

effective_detector_rules.description: IAM group membership frequently grants access to resources and features. Group memberships that have too few members may represent excess privileges being "orphaned".
effective_detector_rules.display_name: IAM group has too few members
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Review the group membership related privileges to ensure that excessive or orphaned privileges are not present.

effective_detector_rules.description: Database system patches often include updates that eliminate known security vulnerabilities. Raise a problem when a database system is discovered which has one or more patches, available for 90 days or more, that have not been applied.

configurations.name: Number of days to apply patch

effective_detector_rules.display_name: Database system patch is not applied
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Oracle recommends that released patches be applied to the DB system as soon as possible.

effective_detector_rules.description: Database patches address functionality, security, and performance issues. The vast majority of security breaches can be prevented by applying available patches.

configurations.name: Number of days to apply patch

effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Oracle recommends that released patches be applied to the database as soon as possible.

effective_detector_rules.description: A back-end set is a logical entity defined by a load balancing policy, a health check policy, and a list of back-end servers.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Load balancer has no back-end set
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that you configure load balancers with back-end sets to control the health and access to a load balancer by defined instances.

effective_detector_rules.description: Prerequisite: Create a Host Scan Recipe and a Host Scan Target in the Scanning service. The Scanning service scans compute hosts to identify known cybersecurity vulnerabilities related to applications, libraries, operating systems, and services. This detector triggers a problem when the Scanning service has reported that an instance has one or more CRITICAL (or lower severity, based on the Input Settings within the detector config) vulnerabilities.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Patch the reported CVE's detected on host by performing actions recommended for each CVE.

effective_detector_rules.description: Encryption of volumes provides an additional level of security on your data. Management of encryption keys is critical to protecting and accessing protected data. Some customers want to identify Block Volumes encrypted Oracle-managed keys in order to apply their own key lifecycle management to the volume.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Block Volume is encrypted with Oracle-managed key
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Assign a vault key to this volume

effective_detector_rules.description: Network security groups (NSGs) act as a virtual firewall for compute instances and other kinds of resources. NSGs outbound (egress) security rules apply to a set of virtual NICs in a VCN to allow access to specific ports and IP addresses.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: NSG egress rule contains disallowed IP/port
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the egress rules for communication with the IP/port are permitted for this NSG.

effective_detector_rules.description: Detector triggers a problem when the write access logs are not enabled for an Object Storage bucket. Access logs help customers secure their sensitive objects by providing visibility into the activities around read and write operations of the objects within the Object storage bucket.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Write Log access disabled for bucket
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure write logs are enabled for the bucket and the logs are being continuously monitored by the security tools.

effective_detector_rules.description: Prerequisite: Create a Host Scan Recipe and a Host Scan Target in the Scanning service. The Scanning service scans compute hosts to identify open ports. This detector triggers a problem when the Scanning service has reported that an instance has one or more open ports. Certain ports are required for operation and delivery of services but any open port beyond the intended list can potentially be used to exploit the services. You can modify the default list of allowed ports or disallowed ports in Input Settings within the detector.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Review if identified ports should be open on this host and close them if they are not required to be open.

effective_detector_rules.description: This detector rule triggers a problem when the protocol configured as part of SSL policy for the load balancer's listener includes any version lesser than TLS 1.2. Older versions of Transport Layer Security are extremely risky and vulnerable to many attacks. The use of TLS 1.2+ is strongly encouraged by several standards like PCI-DSS and NIST.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Load balancer allows weak SSL communication
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the SSL policy version configured for load balancer's listener is at least TLS1.2.

effective_detector_rules.description: A virtual network interface card (VNIC) isa networking component that enables a resource such as a compute instance to connect to a virtual cloud network (VCN). The VNIC determines how the instance connects with endpoints inside and outside the VCN. Each VNIC resides in a subnet in a VCN. An VNIC with an NSG may trigger a connectivity issue.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: VNIC without associated network security group
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the missing NSG association from this VNIC is expected.

effective_detector_rules.description: Default tenancy administrator group members can perform any action on all resources in that tenancy. This high-privilege entitlement must be controlled and restricted to only those users who need it to perform their job functions.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Tenancy admin privilege granted to group
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Verify with the OCI administrator that this entitlement grant was sanctioned and that the membership of the group remains valid after the grant of the administrator privilege.

effective_detector_rules.description: Encryption of storage buckets provides an additional level of security on your data. Management of encryption keys is critical to protecting and accessing protected data. Some customers want to identify storage buckets encrypted Oracle-managed keys in order to apply their own key lifecycle management to the bucket.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Object Storage bucket is encrypted with Oracle-managed key
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Assign a vault key to this bucket

effective_detector_rules.description: Data Safe helps ensure your databases are securely configured. An Oracle cloud database has been discovered that is not yet registered with Data Safe.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Database is not registered in Data Safe
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Register this database instance with Data Safe and configure assessments to evaluate and monitor configuration, check user activities, and mitigate risks.

effective_detector_rules.description: Security lists provide stateful and stateless firewall capability to control network access to your instances. A security list is configured at the subnet level and enforced at the instance level. You can apply multiple security lists to a subnet where a network packet is allowed if it matches any rule in the security lists.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: VCN has no inbound Security List
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that your OCI VCNs use security lists with ingress or inbound rules to only allow access from known resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Object Storage supports anonymous, unauthenticated access to a bucket. A public bucket that has read access enabled for anonymous users allows anyone to obtain object metadata, download bucket objects, and optionally list bucket contents.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the bucket is sanctioned for public access, and if not, direct the OCI administrator to restrict the bucket policy to allow only specific users access to the resources required to accomplish their job functions.

effective_detector_rules.description: OCI load balancers enable end-to-end TLS connections between a client's applications and your VCN. A listener is a logical entity that checks for incoming traffic on the load balancer's IP address. To handle TCP, HTTP, and HTTPS traffic, you must configure at least one listener per traffic type.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Load balancer has no inbound rules or listeners
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that your OCI load balancers use inbound rules or listeners to only allow access from known resources.

effective_detector_rules.description: Use VCN security lists to restrict network access to instances in a subnet. effective_detector_rules.display_name: VCN Security list allows traffic to non-public port from all sources (0.0.0.0/0)
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: To prevent unauthorized access or attacks on compute instances, Oracle recommends that you use a VCN security list to allow SSH or RDP access only from authorized CIDR blocks, rather than leaving them open to the internet (0.0.0.0/0).

effective_detector_rules.description: Changing IAM API keys at least every 90 days is a security best practice. The longer that IAM credentials remain unchanged, the greater the risk that they can become compromised.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Rotate API keys regularly, at least every 90 days.

effective_detector_rules.description: Enabling automatic backup ensures that you will be able to restore the database with minimal data loss, if there is a catastrophic hardware failure.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Database is not backed up automatically
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that automatic backup is enabled.

effective_detector_rules.description: Detector triggers a problem when the read access logs are not enabled for an Object Storage bucket. Access logs help customers secure their sensitive objects by providing visibility into the activities around read and write operations of the objects within the Object storage bucket.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Read Log access disabled for bucket
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure read logs are enabled for the bucket and the logs are being continuously monitored by the security tools.

effective_detector_rules.description: This detector rule triggers a problem when traffic is allowed to certain restricted ports (see Input Settings, Restricted Protocol:Ports List) as part of the Security list ingress rule. If "Restricted Protocol:Ports List" includes port values that are identified or allowed for your workloads, then modify the list of ports in Input Settings accordingly.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: VCN Security list allows traffic to restricted port
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Additional details section of the problem provides a list of open Restricted ports that triggered this problem. Ensure that your OCI VCNs use security lists with ingress or inbound rules to only allow traffic access to identified ports. Review if detected ports should be open on this security list Ingress rule and close them if they are not required to be open. It is also recommended to check the "Restricted Protocol:Ports List" in the Input setting of this detector rule and modify it to allow certain required ports and thus notifying Cloud Guard to not detect a problem for those ports.

effective_detector_rules.description: Detaching a block volume decouples the volume from its associated instance and could affect data available. This could affect data availability from business-critical data to point-in-time copies of volumes as backups.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the block volume is not required to be attached to a compute instance for proper operation.

effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Patch the reported CVE's detected on image by performing actions recommended for each CVE.

effective_detector_rules.description: Use of a public IP address to access a load balancer increases your exposure to potential security and business continuity risks.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: Load Balancer has public IP address
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the load balancer have a public IP address only if it is necessary.

effective_detector_rules.description: Gateways provide external connectivity to hosts in a VCN. They include Local Peering Gateway (LPG) for connectivity to peered VCN.
effective_detector_rules.display_name: VCN has Local Peering Gateway attached
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that local peering gateways are authorized to be attached to a VCN, and that this attachment doesnt expose resources to the internet.

effective_detector_rules.description: The sanctioned version of a database has the most recent security features and vulnerability patches.
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Oracle recommends that the deployed Database version is approved and tested.

effective_detector_rules.display_name: Instance is not running an Oracle public image
effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that your instances are all running sanctioned images from trusted sources.

effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that OCI access by administrators via API keys is performed as an exception. Do not hard code IAM credentials directly in software or documents to a wide audience.

effective_detector_rules.recommendation: Ensure that the policy is restricted to allow only specific users to access the resources required to accomplish their job functions.
